        "text": "CHIPTIC CAVE TEXTILES FROM CHIAPAS, MEXICO\n\nby Irmgard Weitlaner JOHNSON. (Planche II).\n\nThis paper is concerned with the analysis of some Mayan textile fragments recovered from a cave near the Finca elliptic, in the vicinity of Comitan, State of Chiapas. The fragments were found in a sealed jar a number of years ago.\n\nVery few actual specimens are preserved from pre-Spanish times in the Maya area. Other than the finds recovered from the Sacred Cenote at Chichen Itza, and the fragments found in a sealed jar at Cieneguilla, Chiapas l, no Mayan weaves have been reported for Mexico. There are oral reports of other sites in Chiapas where ancient textiles are said to have been recovered ; it would be interesting to examine these specimens for comparative purposes. At Uaxac- tun, Guatemala, Kidder found « imprints of plain bas\"ket-weave cloth » in burials from Tepeu 2. Prints of textiles were also found at Kaminaljuyu on a human effigy vessel and in the clayey earth of tombs 3.\n\nThe importance of the Chiptic cloths is that they give us further direct knowledge of the ancient textile art of the Maya people. They warrant, therefore, a careful examination to determine the details of weaving and patterning methods. The collection comprises three fragmentary pieces which are on display in the Musco Regional de Arqueología e Historia, in Tuxtla Gutierrez, Chiapas (specimens 2-264 I, 2-264 H» 2-264 III4). Furthermore, there is a large three-breadth piece in a private collection, the individual sections of which have been arbitrarily labelled А, В, С There is no doubt, as we shall see below, that all these pieces form part of the same original cloth (fig. 14).\n\nSpecimens I, II, and III are small and irregularly shaped pieces of cotton. They have incomplete length measurements ; only specimen III is furnished with a complete width of 7,5-8 cm. Specimens I and II originally were one piece ; unfortunately it was cut in two with scissors. The largest textile is composed of three separately woven pieces (sections А, В, С) which are seamed"
